*As superuser 
Set permisions 700 to files install-postgresql15.sh  post-install-postgresql15

1.- Run first install script
./install-postgresql15.sh

2.- If previous step finished correctly run the post install script
./post-install-postgresql15

Additionally change the postgres's user password by 'passwd postgres' command
And then change it into the postgresql database enter to the postgres user by 'su - postgres'
and then execute "psql -c "ALTER USER postgres WITH PASSWORD 'StrongPassw0rd';" expected output "ALTER ROLE"

